text:
Exceptionally good service.
Was hesitant upon reading the reviews about horrible service.  However, the next prata place is a distance away.  So, I decided to take the chance and mine! Am I impressed!
Everyone was smiley, including the diners. We were seated immediately like in a restaurant - not something I would expect of a corner coffeshop.  Menu was brought to us  quickly.   Dishes was served with a smile and "Enjoy your meal!".  Everything was fast and efficient from  placing order and paying to the serving of dishes.

Cheese prata is excellent.  Crispy n tasty shredded cheddar cheese.  Maggie goreng is good.  Curry fish is ok.

Atmosphere is a dark tone like a "bar" feel.  Modern pendant lamps.  Clean tables.  Toilets need some work though.

Will come again for sure.

Food here is amazing! Generally no complaints about the food. However, the staff here wasn‚Äôt too friendly. He was impatient and wanted to close accounts as soon as possible, getting me to hurry stuff.

A 24hours Muslim coffee shop. Located at the road hence its easy to find. Many foods items on the menu. We had the simple prata and Thosa for breakfast.  Tables can gets dusty at time road was just infornt of the shop. You can choose to sit indoor or outdoor.  Staffs were friendly. Overall,  a good place for a quick meal. Foods prices was not the cheapest indian Muslim food you can find, but its still reasonable.

Wonder how can they even sell it, satay is 10pcs but they give only 9pcs all which is can not even eat! about the ice horlicks only put the ice on top below still how and burn the pastic cup, the milk powder hasn't even dissolved yet.

Second time receiving bad service from this outlet so i had to feedback. Ordered kway teow goreng special because they said only have goreng and prata, i ask if cheese fries have they said yes. End up fries served cold. I ask staff why the fries so hard and cold, he said because add cheese will be cold. Last time also same staff bad service.
